messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full request paths:
- GET /api/account/{account_id}
- POST /api/account/signup

All HTTP methods acceptable: false

Allowed methods (based on the controller code, not any framework defaults):
- HEAD: false
- POST: true  (mapped by @PostMapping("/signup"))
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true   (mapped by @GetMapping("/{account_id}"))
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller has a class-level @RequestMapping("/api/account"), so every method path is prefixed with /api/account.
- getUserAccountById is annotated @GetMapping("/{account_id}"), therefore the full path is /api/account/{account_id} and GET is explicitly supported. The method uses @PathVariable("account_id"), so the path parameter is {account_id}.
- signupForNewAccount is annotated @PostMapping("/signup"), therefore the full path is /api/account/signup and POST is explicitly supported.
- No methods are annotated for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, or PATCH in this controller; per the instruction to base answers on the code (not on framework behavior like implicit HEAD/OPTIONS handling), those methods are marked not acceptable.
- "All methods" is false because the controller exposes specific mappings (GET and POST) rather than a mapping that allows every HTTP method.
